sentence: Procter & Gamble Co ( PG ) has released its earnings report for the third quarter of 2016.
Procter & Gamble reported earnings per share of 97 cents for Q3 2016.
This is up from the 75 cents it reported during the same time last year.
It also beat analysts' estimate of 82 cents per share for the quarter.
PG's revenue for the third quarter of 2016 came in at $15.75 billion.
This is a drop from the $16.93 billion it reported during the same time last year.
It also didn't match up with Wall Street's estimate of $15.81 billion.
Procter & Gamble said that its EPS for Q4 2016 will be lower than last year.
It expects negative effects from increased advertising costs, currency headwinds, a higher tax rate and lower non-operating income.
PG shares were down 1% as of Tuesday morning.
